From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@example.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 19:05:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] nfpm: depend on Kong install tree

The nFPM package action creates `nfpm-prefix` as a symlink to Bazel's
`bazel-out/.../build/kong-dev` install tree, but it did not declare
`//build:kong` as an input.

After `bazel clean --expunge`, directly building `//:kong_deb` can therefore
run nFPM before the Kong install tree exists.  nFPM then fails with:

  matching "./nfpm-prefix/bin": file does not exist

Declare `//build:kong` as a hidden input of the package rule so `//:kong_deb`
properly depends on the install tree.  Also declare the nFPM config file as an
input of the action that reads it.
---
 build/nfpm/rules.bzl | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/build/nfpm/rules.bzl b/build/nfpm/rules.bzl
index 951b4f0..a38cb16 100644
--- a/build/nfpm/rules.bzl
+++ b/build/nfpm/rules.bzl
@@ -36,7 +36,7 @@ def _nfpm_pkg_impl(ctx):
     build_destdir = ctx.var["BINDIR"] + "/build/" + KONG_VAR["BUILD_NAME"]
 
     ctx.actions.run_shell(
-        inputs = ctx.files._nfpm_bin,
+        inputs = ctx.files._nfpm_bin + ctx.files._kong_build + [ctx.file.config],
         mnemonic = "nFPM",
         command = "ln -sf %s nfpm-prefix; external/nfpm/nfpm $@" % build_destdir,
         arguments = [nfpm_args],
@@ -75,6 +75,9 @@ nfpm_pkg = rule(
         "_nfpm_bin": attr.label(
             default = "@nfpm//:all_srcs",
         ),
+        "_kong_build": attr.label(
+            default = "//build:kong",
+        ),
         "_cc_toolchain": attr.label(
             default = "@bazel_tools//tools/cpp:current_cc_toolchain",
         ),
-- 
